      "text": "Remove and inspect wiper/washer switch"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If there are components of the SRS airbag system in the vicinity, refer to the work precautions and configuration drawings described for the SRS airbag system before proceeding."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Column cover removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000786",
          "label": "Column cover removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Wiper/washer switch removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1010_5.0_jpn_11580871_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). While pressing the tab, remove the wiper/washer switch (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Wiper/washer switch Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect the continuity between terminals in each position of the coupler (A) and confirm that there is continuity only between ○ and ○. If there is no continuity, replace wiper/washer switch (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
